pages.title: Channel Catfish
pages.text: The channel catfish ($(o)Ictalurus punctatus$()) is North America's most numerous catfish species.$(br2)It is the official fish of Kansas, Missouri, Iowa, Nebraska, and Tennessee, and is informally referred to as a "channel cat".
